chapters.title: Professor Laurence Eaves, CBE FRS Expertise includes electrons, electric fields, quantom dots & graphene
Professor Philip Moriarty Expertise includes nanoscience & single atom/molecule manipulation
Professor Martyn Poliakoff, CBE FRS Award-winning chemistry researcher & Foreign Secretary of the Royal Society
Professor Ed Copeland Cosmologist and expert on inflation, cosmic strings & the early Universe
Associate Professor Tony Padilla Work includes scalar tensor theory & modified gravity Liverpool FC season ticket holder

description:
We showed a few professors (of physics and chemistry) the popular game 2048 - none of them had heard of it!
More links & stuff in full description below 

The Professors, from the University of Nottingham, are:
Laurence Eaves, Martyn Poliakoff, Phil Moriarty, Ed Copeland and Tony Padilla.

Raw game footage: http://youtu.be/3a-i36y1l4A
PLAY THE GAME: http://bit.ly/2048num
And of those who prefer Threes! ---http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Threes!

You can see more of them here on Numberphile, along with our physics channel sixtysymbols and chemistry channel periodicvideos.

https://www.youtube.com/periodicvideos
http://www.youtube.com/sixtysymbols

Knight's Tour: http://youtu.be/ab_dY3dZFHM
